display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)]]></fr:tex> be an irreducible polynomial of degree <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d\mathrel {\bigm |} n]]></fr:tex>. Then
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}_{p}[x]/(f(x))\cong \mathbb {F}_{p^{d}},]]></fr:tex>
which is isomorphic to a subfield of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}_{p^{n}}]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)]]></fr:tex> has a root in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}_{p^{n}}]]></fr:tex>, hence splits completely over it since <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}_{p^{n}} / \mathbb {F}_{p}]]></fr:tex> is Galois. But then every root of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)]]></fr:tex> (being an element of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}_{p^{n}}]]></fr:tex>) is a root of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x^{p^{n}}-x]]></fr:tex>. Since <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)]]></fr:tex> is separable, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)\mathrel {\bigm |}(x^{p^{n}}-x)]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
<fr:p>Suppose <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)]]></fr:tex> is irreducible over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}_{p}]]></fr:tex> and suppose it divides <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x^{p^{n}}-x]]></fr:tex>. Then its splitting field is contained in <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}_{p^{n}}]]></fr:tex> and must be isomorphic to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}_{p^{d}}]]></fr:tex> for some <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d]]></fr:tex> which divides <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d\mathrel {\bigm |} n]]></fr:tex>. But since <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}_{p^{d}}]]></fr:tex> is Galois, it must be isomorphic to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}_{p}[x]/(f(x))]]></fr:tex>, hence <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x)]]></fr:tex> has degree <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[d]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
<fr:p>Since <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[x^{p^{n}}-x]]></fr:tex> is separable, it's the product of all distinct irreducible factors.</fr:p><html:span
